          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Fig. of cross-section vs. neutron wavelength and energy",
                "of range 2.2 eV to 7 milli-eV is given in journal",
                "Atomkernenergie/Kerntechnik vol. 42 (1983) No. 2,",
                "p. 105. At neutron energies between 1.2 eV to 0.20 eV,",
                "the cross section behaviour showed an evidence for",
                "1/v thermal slope given as:",
                "     sig = ((8.40 +- 0.29) +- (1.54 +- 0.06)/root(E)) B"
              ]
